	<section>
      <id>s1</id>
      <audio_location>dif05stsp22.mp3</audio_location>
      <audio_text>On the 737 MAX, pitch stability augmentation is provided by the Maneuvering Characteristics Augmentation System (MCAS) function in the Speed Trim System. It is designed to operate at elevated angles of attack (AOAs) when the autopilot is not engaged and the flaps are UP.</audio_text>
      <instruction>
      </instruction>
      <completion>both</completion>
      <advance>auto</advance>
    </section>
	<section>
      <id>s2</id>
      <audio_location>dif05stsp22a.mp3</audio_location>
      <audio_text>The purpose of the MCAS function is to increase control column forces by commanding the stabilizer in the nose down direction at elevated AOAs.</audio_text>
      <instruction>
      </instruction>
      <completion>both</completion>
      <advance>auto</advance>
    </section>
